00:01:44.139 --> 00:01:46.860
They'll tell us all of the reasons logically

00:01:46.860 --> 00:01:51.860
and going through the process of trying to analyze something

00:01:52.160 --> 00:01:55.639
and the analytical minded people and say, no, no, no,

00:01:55.639 --> 00:01:56.919
you have to follow this.

00:01:56.919 --> 00:01:57.760
You can't trust that.

00:01:57.760 --> 00:02:01.199
And the reality is that David says in the Lord,

00:02:01.199 --> 00:02:02.440
put I my trust.

00:02:02.440 --> 00:02:05.279
As we begin focusing on verse number two this evening,

00:02:05.279 --> 00:02:08.720
we find that David would continue to trust the Lord,

00:02:08.720 --> 00:02:11.000
which would result in rest.

00:02:11.000 --> 00:02:14.580
And what a blessing to know that we're in the hands of God,

00:02:14.580 --> 00:02:17.559
that I've put my trust in the Lord, Jehovah God,

00:02:17.559 --> 00:02:18.960
the self-existent one,

00:02:18.960 --> 00:02:21.660
the one who said, let there be light and there is light.

00:02:22.479 --> 00:02:25.839
But verse number two, as we begin to unfold this Psalm,

00:02:25.839 --> 00:02:28.960
enables us to understand with greater clarity,

00:02:28.960 --> 00:02:32.279
the circumstances that David was dealing with.

00:02:32.279 --> 00:02:34.320
Notice what the Bible says in verse number two,

00:02:34.320 --> 00:02:36.699
it'll be our focus of our study this evening.

00:02:36.699 --> 00:02:41.699
The Bible says for lo, the wicked bend their bow,

00:02:42.119 --> 00:02:45.279
they make ready their arrow upon the string

00:02:45.279 --> 00:02:50.000
that they may privilege shoot at the upright in heart.

00:02:50.020 --> 00:02:52.820
In verse number two, we find that there are two categories

00:02:52.820 --> 00:02:54.639
of people that are referenced to us.

00:02:54.639 --> 00:02:56.500
The first is the wicked.

00:02:56.500 --> 00:02:59.059
We could also refer to them as being the ungodly.

00:02:59.059 --> 00:03:00.860
In fact, throughout the Psalms,

00:03:00.860 --> 00:03:03.100
you'll find that those words sometimes,

00:03:03.100 --> 00:03:05.339
many times are used interchangeably.

00:03:05.339 --> 00:03:07.539
And we find that he speaks about the wicked

00:03:07.539 --> 00:03:09.000
in verse number two.

00:03:09.000 --> 00:03:13.139
And he then also speaks about the upright in heart.

00:03:13.139 --> 00:03:15.699
If we would say that the wicked are the ungodly,

00:03:15.699 --> 00:03:18.220
we would say that the upright in heart are the righteous.

00:03:18.320 --> 00:03:21.440
And so we find that there's these two categories of people

00:03:21.440 --> 00:03:24.199
that are introduced to us in verse number two.

00:03:24.199 --> 00:03:26.880
And as we study this verse of scripture this evening,

00:03:26.880 --> 00:03:28.679
I've simply titled the message,

00:03:28.679 --> 00:03:31.880
the thought this evening under attack.

00:03:31.880 --> 00:03:34.440
I wonder, do you ever feel like you're under attack?

00:03:34.440 --> 00:03:35.720
You say, man, every day,

00:03:35.720 --> 00:03:38.160
all the time I feel like I'm under attack.

00:03:38.160 --> 00:03:40.720
And this is right in my wheelhouse.

00:03:40.720 --> 00:03:43.000
You're dealing with what I'm facing today.

00:03:43.000 --> 00:03:46.479
And the reality is that there are times in which seasons

00:03:46.479 --> 00:03:49.300
in which it seems like we're constantly being bombarded,

00:03:49.300 --> 00:03:50.820
that we're under attack.

00:03:50.820 --> 00:03:53.199
We understand that we have an enemy,

00:03:53.199 --> 00:03:55.220
but as we look at this text of scripture,

00:03:55.220 --> 00:03:58.779
we're reminded that it's not simply the enemy,

00:03:58.779 --> 00:04:02.779
although he is actively seeking whom he may devour,

00:04:02.779 --> 00:04:04.619
but there is a great contrast.

00:04:04.619 --> 00:04:07.139
There's a great conflict in the world

00:04:07.139 --> 00:04:09.860
between the ungodly or the wicked

00:04:09.860 --> 00:04:12.539
and the upright in the heart or the righteous.

00:04:12.539 --> 00:04:14.860
And we'll look at some things that Jesus said

00:04:14.880 --> 00:04:15.839
in the gospel of John,

00:04:15.839 --> 00:04:18.559
as we make our way through the message this evening.

00:04:18.559 --> 00:04:20.399
But as we look at this text of scripture,

00:04:20.399 --> 00:04:23.279
verse two and consider under attack,

00:04:23.279 --> 00:04:25.339
I want you to see number one, if you're taking notes,

00:04:25.339 --> 00:04:29.119
a plan uncovered, a plan uncovered.

00:04:29.119 --> 00:04:30.920
Why is it that we deal with this?

00:04:30.920 --> 00:04:34.760
And why do I use the verbiage that I use

00:04:34.760 --> 00:04:36.559
as a plan being uncovered?

00:04:36.559 --> 00:04:41.119
Well, because the reality is that though our enemy is subtle

00:04:41.119 --> 00:04:42.839
and though he is clever,

00:04:42.859 --> 00:04:46.260
though the wicked are operating with subtlety here,

00:04:46.260 --> 00:04:48.859
it talks about being may privilege shoot

00:04:48.859 --> 00:04:50.160
at the upright in heart.

00:04:50.160 --> 00:04:52.820
We understand that God has exposed

00:04:52.820 --> 00:04:56.179
or uncovered the plan of the wicked.

00:04:56.179 --> 00:04:59.059
We find that God has told us,

00:04:59.059 --> 00:05:02.220
even as we mentioned before in Psalm two,

00:05:02.220 --> 00:05:04.059
where the Bible talks about those

00:05:04.059 --> 00:05:06.019
that have gathered themselves together,

00:05:06.019 --> 00:05:10.220
the heathen rage and the people imagine a vain thing

00:05:10.239 --> 00:05:13.480
and how they take counsel together against the Lord

00:05:13.480 --> 00:05:15.279
and all that takes place.

00:05:15.279 --> 00:05:20.279
And so God has uncovered the plan of the enemy.

00:05:20.760 --> 00:05:23.119
And we find that as we look throughout the scriptures,

00:05:23.119 --> 00:05:25.559
in fact, the part of the text that I'll be preaching

00:05:25.559 --> 00:05:27.320
on this upcoming Sunday morning

00:05:27.320 --> 00:05:29.760
in first Corinthians chapter two,

00:05:29.760 --> 00:05:32.880
Paul says this, that we're not ignorant of his devices,

00:05:32.880 --> 00:05:36.839
speaking about the methodologies, if you will, of the enemy.

00:05:36.839 --> 00:05:38.200
As you study through the scriptures,

00:05:38.220 --> 00:05:42.019
it's amazing to find the many ways in which God reveals

00:05:42.019 --> 00:05:46.899
or exposes to us, uncovers the plan of the enemy.

00:05:46.899 --> 00:05:49.179
Notice in the verse of scripture, it says this,

00:05:49.179 --> 00:05:50.420
when we talk about their plan,

00:05:50.420 --> 00:05:51.660
we see that they're prepared.

00:05:51.660 --> 00:05:55.980
The Bible says that the wicked bend their bow.

00:05:55.980 --> 00:05:57.260
Not only do they bend their bow,

00:05:57.260 --> 00:06:00.779
but notice it says they make ready their arrow

00:06:00.779 --> 00:06:04.359
upon the string and they are prepared.

00:06:04.359 --> 00:06:06.500
They have bent their bow.

00:06:06.519 --> 00:06:08.200
They've made ready their arrows.

00:06:08.200 --> 00:06:12.519
The Bible continues to say that they may privily shoot

00:06:12.519 --> 00:06:15.380
at the upright in heart.

00:06:15.380 --> 00:06:17.880
We find that there are times in which it seems like

00:06:17.880 --> 00:06:19.640
in certain arenas of our lives,

00:06:19.640 --> 00:06:20.959
in certain circumstances,

00:06:20.959 --> 00:06:23.079
and David, we're getting ready to look at some things

00:06:23.079 --> 00:06:24.839
that David was facing personally

00:06:24.839 --> 00:06:28.440
and why he shared with us this truth this evening,

00:06:28.440 --> 00:06:31.399
but we find that this plan is being uncovered.

00:06:31.399 --> 00:06:33.160
It's being exposed.

00:06:33.160 --> 00:06:35.760
And we find that there are times in which we live

00:06:35.779 --> 00:06:39.339
and it seems like the enemy is just actively watching

00:06:39.339 --> 00:06:43.940
and waiting for just one misstep so that they can pounce.

00:06:43.940 --> 00:06:45.380
We're under a microscope,

00:06:45.380 --> 00:06:48.239
it seems like at times in our lives.

00:06:48.239 --> 00:06:51.760
We find here that this plan is uncovered.

00:06:51.760 --> 00:06:53.399
David was aware.

00:06:53.399 --> 00:06:56.899
He had already declared that in the Lord put on my trust.

00:06:56.899 --> 00:06:59.519
And he says that the wicked, they bend their bow.

00:06:59.519 --> 00:07:01.299
They make ready their arrow upon the string.

00:07:01.299 --> 00:07:05.420
They may privily shoot at the upright in heart.

00:07:06.079 --> 00:07:07.320
As we'd say that there's a plan uncovered,

00:07:07.320 --> 00:07:08.200
I would say number two,

00:07:08.200 --> 00:07:11.359
and we'll spend the majority of our time here this evening,

00:07:11.359 --> 00:07:15.480
a principle understood, a principle understood.

00:07:15.480 --> 00:07:16.959
As we look at this verse of scripture,

00:07:16.959 --> 00:07:19.920
we find that God uncovers their plan,

00:07:19.920 --> 00:07:23.440
but then he explains to us and helps us to understand

00:07:23.440 --> 00:07:26.279
a biblical principle that is so vital for us

00:07:26.279 --> 00:07:28.480
to incorporate in our lives,

00:07:28.480 --> 00:07:32.160
that as we walk this Christian life,

00:07:32.160 --> 00:07:35.200
