And Saul said, blessed be of the Lord

00:25:03.440 --> 00:25:05.300
for you have compassion on me.

00:25:05.300 --> 00:25:08.200
Go, I pray you prepare yet and know

00:25:08.200 --> 00:25:10.860
and see his place where his haunt is.

00:25:10.860 --> 00:25:13.100
And who have seen him there for it has told me

00:25:13.100 --> 00:25:15.240
that he deal with very subtly.

00:25:15.240 --> 00:25:18.360
See therefore and take knowledge of all the lurking places

00:25:18.360 --> 00:25:20.559
where he hideth himself and come ye again to me

00:25:20.559 --> 00:25:23.360
with the certainty and I will go with you.

00:25:23.360 --> 00:25:25.100
So he's sending out people.

00:25:25.100 --> 00:25:28.040
He can't find these folks in the David

00:25:28.040 --> 00:25:30.120
in the wilderness of Ziph and the wood of Ziph

00:25:30.120 --> 00:25:33.279
because of just all of the difficulty there.

00:25:33.279 --> 00:25:35.059
So he's got these folks that are gonna help him.

00:25:35.059 --> 00:25:37.240
Notice where he says at the end of verse 23,

00:25:37.240 --> 00:25:38.840
that I will search him out

00:25:38.840 --> 00:25:41.940
throughout all the thousands of Judah.

00:25:42.940 --> 00:25:46.360
Saul made his number one priority and goal

00:25:48.760 --> 00:25:51.840
was to kill David, was to kill David.

00:25:52.960 --> 00:25:56.460
No wonder David said as he spoke to Samuel

00:25:57.340 --> 00:26:00.380
there's but a step between me and death.

00:26:00.380 --> 00:26:04.820
You know he really wasn't being in a place of exaggerating.

00:26:04.820 --> 00:26:06.340
There are times in which we exaggerate

00:26:06.340 --> 00:26:09.340
the circumstances really as they are.

00:26:10.340 --> 00:26:13.660
But truly David was but a step between him and death.

00:26:13.660 --> 00:26:17.900
I mean Saul had everything, all the resources,

00:26:17.900 --> 00:26:19.320
the mightiest of men.

00:26:19.320 --> 00:26:22.420
I mean he was coming after David.

00:26:22.420 --> 00:26:23.720
The Bible says in verse 24,

00:26:23.720 --> 00:26:26.779
and they arose and went to Ziph before Saul.

00:26:26.779 --> 00:26:29.180
But David and his men were in the wilderness of Maon

00:26:29.180 --> 00:26:31.480
in the plain of the south of Jeshamon.

00:26:31.480 --> 00:26:33.779
Saul also and his men went to seek him

00:26:33.779 --> 00:26:35.500
and they told David wherefore he came down

00:26:35.500 --> 00:26:38.160
into a rock and a boat in the wilderness of Maon.

00:26:38.160 --> 00:26:40.920
And when Saul heard that he pursued after David

00:26:40.920 --> 00:26:42.559
in the wilderness of Maon

00:26:42.559 --> 00:26:44.279
and Saul went on this side of the mountain

00:26:44.279 --> 00:26:47.480
and David and his men on that side of the mountain.

00:26:47.480 --> 00:26:50.559
And David made haste to get away for fear of Saul.

00:26:50.559 --> 00:26:52.840
For Saul and his men compassed David

00:26:52.840 --> 00:26:55.100
and his men round about to take them.

00:26:58.720 --> 00:27:03.720
But God, because the enemy attacks and God defends.

00:27:04.240 --> 00:27:08.320
Notice the Bible says in verse 27,

00:27:08.320 --> 00:27:10.600
but there came a messenger unto Saul.

00:27:10.600 --> 00:27:11.680
Isn't that amazing?

00:27:12.600 --> 00:27:14.040
I mean, just pause for a moment

00:27:14.040 --> 00:27:15.800
and consider where they are.

00:27:15.800 --> 00:27:18.860
He's removed from the place

00:27:18.860 --> 00:27:22.260
in which the Philistines are going to begin attacking.

00:27:22.260 --> 00:27:23.960
We'll look at it in here just a moment.

00:27:23.960 --> 00:27:26.760
But we find that just at that moment,

00:27:26.760 --> 00:27:30.120
when David's location is found out

00:27:30.120 --> 00:27:33.020
and David has been on that side and Saul on this side

00:27:33.420 --> 00:27:34.620
and all that's going on.

00:27:34.620 --> 00:27:38.660
And now David is seeking to get away.

00:27:38.660 --> 00:27:39.500
Why?

00:27:39.500 --> 00:27:40.320
Because he's surrounded.

00:27:40.320 --> 00:27:43.900
He's compassed David and his men round about to take them.

00:27:43.900 --> 00:27:47.779
And at that very moment, a messenger shows up.

00:27:48.980 --> 00:27:49.820
Who is Saul?

00:27:49.820 --> 00:27:51.580
Well, Saul's the king.

00:27:51.580 --> 00:27:54.340
And Saul has responsibility as the king.

00:27:54.340 --> 00:27:56.020
One of his greatest responsibilities

00:27:56.020 --> 00:27:58.460
is for the welfare of the nation.

00:27:58.460 --> 00:27:59.500
He's the king.

00:28:00.500 --> 00:28:03.020
He's not concerned about the welfare of the nation

00:28:03.020 --> 00:28:05.180
because he's concerned about killing David.

00:28:07.320 --> 00:28:10.700
We find that the Bible says that this messenger comes to Saul

00:28:10.700 --> 00:28:12.900
and notice what he says in verse 27,

00:28:12.900 --> 00:28:16.059
haste thee and come.

00:28:16.059 --> 00:28:16.940
Why?

00:28:16.940 --> 00:28:21.020
For the Philistines have invaded the land.

00:28:21.020 --> 00:28:23.660
I don't know how long it would have taken a messenger

00:28:23.660 --> 00:28:27.220
to get from where they started to where Saul was located.

00:28:27.220 --> 00:28:30.500
I don't know how long the Philistines had to be gathering

00:28:30.500 --> 00:28:32.100
before they started to attack.

00:28:32.100 --> 00:28:34.460
But what I know is that the very moment

00:28:34.460 --> 00:28:36.220
that God needed to step in

00:28:36.220 --> 00:28:38.900
and do something miraculous for David,

00:28:38.900 --> 00:28:40.419
the messenger showed up.

00:28:42.739 --> 00:28:45.200
That's how our God works.

00:28:45.200 --> 00:28:47.020
That's who our God is.

00:28:49.380 --> 00:28:51.020
And the Bible says in verse 28,

00:28:51.020 --> 00:28:56.020
wherefore Saul returned from pursuing after David.

00:28:58.100 --> 00:29:00.980
The enemy attacks, but God defends.

00:29:01.900 --> 00:29:03.540
And as we look at this Psalm

00:29:03.540 --> 00:29:06.859
and as we begin to make progress

00:29:06.859 --> 00:29:09.220
through the passage of scripture

00:29:09.220 --> 00:29:11.820
and understanding the principles

00:29:11.820 --> 00:29:13.900
that God has for us in our lives,

00:29:13.900 --> 00:29:16.380
and we see that David is writing

00:29:16.380 --> 00:29:18.460
and he's writing from no doubt

00:29:18.460 --> 00:29:20.280
some experience that he's had.

00:29:20.280 --> 00:29:21.739
And I just wonder this evening

00:29:21.739 --> 00:29:23.700
as we take the principles,

00:29:23.700 --> 00:29:25.619
as we read the example

00:29:25.619 --> 00:29:28.700
and the experience of David this evening,

00:29:28.700 --> 00:29:30.840
how does it impact us?

00:29:34.140 --> 00:29:36.739
Because there are times in which we're under attack.

00:29:38.580 --> 00:29:40.040
What do we do?

00:29:40.040 --> 00:29:42.500
Do we listen to the people that are saying flee?

00:29:43.460 --> 00:29:45.619
Or do we stand with resolve and say in the Lord,

00:29:45.619 --> 00:29:46.900
put I my trust.

00:29:47.799 --> 00:29:48.880
I'm trusting God.

00:29:49.880 --> 00:29:51.980
And I know that the enemy is gonna attack,

00:29:52.919 --> 00:29:55.020
but I know that my God's going to defend.

00:29:56.059 --> 00:29:57.900
And it's such an amazing truth

00:29:57.900 --> 00:29:59.859
that we see in the life of David.

00:29:59.859 --> 00:30:01.779
Now, David's a man.

00:30:01.779 --> 00:30:05.779
At one point in his life after this, we find that he goes to Philistine territory.

00:30:05.779 --> 00:30:08.539
It's a sad situation.

00:30:08.539 --> 00:30:14.619
There are times in which we can be overwhelmed, but how important it is that we declare our

00:30:14.619 --> 00:30:19.779
trust in the Lord, and though we understand that we're under attack, though we understand

00:30:19.779 --> 00:30:25.139
what's taking place, listen, we love those that do not know the Lord because we want

00:30:25.139 --> 00:30:28.599
to see them say, we want to take the gospel to them and share the truth of the gospel

00:30:28.599 --> 00:30:34.919
that they too might be saved and go to heaven.

00:30:34.919 --> 00:30:41.859
But Jesus said, the world's going to hate you because you're not of the world.

00:30:41.859 --> 00:30:45.959
And I know that you have found it to be the case as you live life, that the more you try

00:30:45.959 --> 00:30:54.159
to be a light, the more you find out that men love darkness rather than light.

00:30:54.279 --> 00:31:00.599
This evening, we find that though the enemy, their plan is uncovered, we already know how

00:31:00.599 --> 00:31:05.959
the enemy is going to operate, but we know that our God's going to defend.

00:31:05.959 --> 00:31:13.639
This evening, we must take great comfort in recognizing this principle and applying it

00:31:13.639 --> 00:31:21.959
in our own lives, Lord, no matter what may come, help me to continue to trust you and

00:31:21.959 --> 00:31:28.559
to rest in you because though the enemy attacks, the Lord defends.

00:31:28.559 --> 00:31:29.559
Let's pray together.

00:31:29.559 --> 00:31:30.559
Father, we love you.

00:31:30.559 --> 00:31:31.559
We thank you for loving us.

00:31:31.559 --> 00:31:33.519
Thank you for your word tonight.

00:31:33.519 --> 00:31:43.799
We thank you for the principle to be understood, and God, I pray that as we consider the truth

00:31:43.799 --> 00:31:48.839
from this verse of Scripture and from the life of David that you would help us as we

00:31:48.839 --> 00:31:53.319
live this Christian life, Lord, help us to trust you.

00:31:53.319 --> 00:31:58.639
Let come what may, help us to trust you.

00:31:58.639 --> 00:32:06.039
Help us, Lord, to know, to recognize and understand that the enemy will attack, but God, you are

00:32:06.039 --> 00:32:10.519
our defense and how we rejoice in that.

00:32:10.519 --> 00:32:15.199
We thank you that you're a very present help at the time of trouble.

00:32:15.199 --> 00:32:18.999
We thank you that you'll never leave us nor forsake us.

00:32:18.999 --> 00:32:25.239
We thank you for recording for us the events in David's life that we can gain encouragement

00:32:25.239 --> 00:32:27.879
from them.

00:32:27.879 --> 00:32:31.879
Thank you now for this time that we have in our midweek service for corporate prayer.

00:32:31.879 --> 00:32:33.719
I pray, God, that you would meet with us.

00:32:33.719 --> 00:32:38.999
I pray that you would bless every aspect of the prayer time.

00:32:38.999 --> 00:32:40.299
I pray that you'd be glorified.

00:32:40.299 --> 00:32:41.959
We thank you that you hear an answer prayer.

00:32:41.959 --> 00:32:46.559
We thank you that you're able to do exceeding abundantly above all that we ask or think.

00:32:46.559 --> 00:32:50.719
Would you move and work as only you can, and we'll be careful to give the honor and glory

00:32:50.719 --> 00:32:54.439
for it's in Christ's name we pray, amen.

00:32:54.439 --> 00:32:55.599
Does anyone need a bulletin tonight?

